Use of Spring Security source code and documentation
---------------------------------------------------

Spring Security is an upstream project maintained by its respective
owners and contributors. This project does not claim ownership of the
Spring Security source code or documentation.

This project may fetch, build, parse, or index content from the official
Spring Security repository and documentation for the limited purpose of
documentation-oriented search and retrieval through MCP tools.

The Spring Security repository is treated as an upstream source for
documentation indexing, not as code owned or maintained by this project.

If documentation text is extracted into an index, it should be used to
support search, retrieval, citation, and navigation back to the official
documentation.

Where possible, returned or indexed content should preserve attribution
metadata such as:

- upstream repository URL
- official documentation URL
- documentation version or branch
- commit SHA
- build timestamp
- heading path or page title

For authoritative information, users should refer to the official Spring
Security documentation and the official Spring Security source repository.

